Jim and Martha are standing together at the corner of a rectangular field. Jim walks diagonally across the field, while Martha gets to the same location by walking along the field's length and width. The field is 300 feet wide and 400 feet long. The problem is to determine how many feet less than Martha does Jim walk.The rectangular field can be represented using the following LaTeX diagram: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) rectangle (4,3);\draw (0,0) -- (4,3);
ode at (2,1.5) {$d$};
ode at (2,-0.3) {400 ft};
ode at (-0.3,1.5) {300 ft};\end{tikzpicture}where $d$ represents the diagonal path taken by Jim.
